The White House is making plans for the 2019 Christmas season. First Lady Melania Trump and President Donald J. Trump will open the White House to the public for traditional Christmas decorating. Individuals can apply to volunteer to decorate the White House or serve as a greeter during the Holiday Open Houses. Musicians, such as high school bands, choirs, and Christmas-themed entertainers, are also invited to apply to perform during the Holiday Open Houses in December. The deadline to apply for volunteering is August 27, 2019, and the deadline for entertainment applications is September 10, 2019. All applicants will be notified of their status in September and October respectively. Any questions should be directed to Volunteers@who.eop.gov.